tainability transitions) could provide beachhead before broader expansion.", "swot": {"strengths": ["Genuine understanding of professional certification pain point from career development background", "Conceptually differentiated approach (outcome-driven rather than course-driven)", "Favorable market timing with credential inflation and AI disruption trends", "Multiple revenue stream potential (B2C premium, B2B enterprise)", "Clear articulation of the problem and proposed solution"], "weaknesses": ["Zero traction—no validation of product-market fit", "Solo founder with capacity and skill gap risks across all functions", "Long timeline to data moat creation leaves window of vulnerability", "Content-first strategy delays monetization and requires patience", "Unclear premium pricing tier differentiation ($19-49 is a wide range)", "Multiple target segments (B2C, B2B, multiple career stages) may dilute focus", "No technical capabilities or proprietary data sources specified"], "opportunities": ["First-mover potential in outcome-driven credential mapping if executed quickly", "Secular trends (AI disruption, credential inflation, professional accountability demand) create tailwind", "B2B enterprise path with higher revenue per customer and stickier relationships", "Network effect from user-contributed outcomes could create defensible moat", "Expansion into hiring matching, credential verification provides long-term growth", "Niche verticals (tech, healthcare, sustainability) could provide initial beachhead", "Low-cost customer acquisition through content-first SEO strategy"], "threats": ["Well-resourced competitors (Coursera, LinkedIn Learning, Udemy) could replicate the model", "Incumbent platforms have existing distribution, brand, and user trust advantages", "Chicken-and-egg problem: users need value before contributing data, platform needs data before providing value", "B2B enterprise sales cycle is long and complex for early-stage startup", "Professionals may be satis